00:07:00.300 --> 00:07:02.210
I will make it a reality.

00:07:02.600 --> 00:07:05.500
Those are Master's orders, 
and I will obey them.

00:07:13.570 --> 00:07:15.890
What the hell am I supposed to do?!

00:07:15.890 --> 00:07:17.070
Maybe drink less.

00:07:17.070 --> 00:07:20.080
I just want her to look forward again.

00:07:20.080 --> 00:07:22.500
So I busted my butt for her training plan!

00:07:22.500 --> 00:07:25.040
I tried to come up with the 
best possible race plan, too!

00:07:25.040 --> 00:07:25.940
But...

00:07:25.940 --> 00:07:27.030
She's been "fine."

00:07:27.030 --> 00:07:30.180
Right! She's been doing a 
"fine" job of everything!

00:07:30.180 --> 00:07:32.250
But there's not a hint of the old Teio spark!

00:07:32.250 --> 00:07:35.710
I know her passion for 
racing can't be gone.

00:07:35.710 --> 00:07:36.910
But...

00:07:36.910 --> 00:07:38.570
What am I supposed to do?!

00:07:38.570 --> 00:07:39.800
Unbelievable.

00:07:39.800 --> 00:07:41.320
I'm also broke.

00:07:41.830 --> 00:07:43.290
Get a grip, would you?!

00:07:44.540 --> 00:07:49.130
You managed to work through Tokai Teio's 
injury at the derby, didn't you?

00:07:49.340 --> 00:07:50.580
But...

00:07:50.580 --> 00:07:53.330
But she couldn't achieve 
her Triple Crown dream,

00:07:53.330 --> 00:07:55.830
and her dream of being 
undefeated is gone now, too.

00:07:55.830 --> 00:07:57.250
Do you realize how few horse girls

00:07:57.250 --> 00:08:00.740
can make their dreams from before 
they start racing a reality?

00:08:01.230 --> 00:08:04.310
And dreams can take different 
shapes over time.

00:08:05.510 --> 00:08:09.040
If she can get through this, 
Tokai Teio will be even stronger.

00:08:10.360 --> 00:08:13.320
You need to have some faith 
in her in the meantime.

00:08:13.320 --> 00:08:14.630
Ow, ow, ow...

00:08:14.630 --> 00:08:15.740
I'm heading out.

00:08:16.480 --> 00:08:18.200
Thank you for coming by.

00:08:19.280 --> 00:08:20.300
Thanks.

00:08:26.300 --> 00:08:27.280
Bartender...

00:08:27.280 --> 00:08:28.170
Yes?

00:08:28.420 --> 00:08:30.460
You got any glasses that need washing?

00:08:32.880 --> 00:08:35.150
There's quite a few to go 
to cover your tab, you know.

00:08:35.150 --> 00:08:36.890
I've got it handled!

00:08:36.890 --> 00:08:40.160
Teio, I'm gonna make sure 
you make your comeback!

00:08:42.350 --> 00:08:44.560
Bourbon-san!

00:08:43.370 --> 00:08:44.560
You can do it!

00:08:44.560 --> 00:08:45.500
Come on!

00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:47.060
Go, Bourbon!

00:08:48.050 --> 00:08:49.520
Mihono Bourbon is out in front!

00:08:49.520 --> 00:08:52.310
Rice Shower is moving up, 
along with Machikane Tannhäuser!

00:08:52.310 --> 00:08:53.990
Mihono Bourbon is maintaining a narrow lead!

00:08:53.990 --> 00:08:55.410
But Rice Shower closing in on the outside!

00:08:55.410 --> 00:08:56.700
Machikane Tannhäuser moves up the inside!

00:08:56.700 --> 00:08:58.270
Rice Shower and Tannhäuser!

00:08:58.270 --> 00:08:59.550
Rice Shower's taken the lead!

00:08:59.550 --> 00:09:00.660
And she takes the goal!

00:09:00.260 --> 00:09:00.660
Kikkashou

00:09:01.420 --> 00:09:04.660
Mihono Bourbon is unable 
to claim her Triple Crown!

00:09:02.640 --> 00:09:04.660
Are you kidding me?!

00:09:04.660 --> 00:09:07.620
The Kikkashou's winning 
horse girl is Rice Shower!

00:09:15.100 --> 00:09:17.430
Wait, what?

00:09:17.430 --> 00:09:20.010
Unfortunately, you lost your 
chance at the Triple Crown.

00:09:20.240 --> 00:09:21.100
Yes.

00:09:21.100 --> 00:09:23.770
I'm sorry I was unable to live 
up to Master's expectations.

00:09:23.770 --> 00:09:27.140
But, I believe I have 
gained something in this loss.

00:09:27.140 --> 00:09:28.650
Next time, I will win.

00:09:28.650 --> 00:09:31.010
Uh, Bourbon-san? Wait!

00:09:31.750 --> 00:09:34.510
Gain something... by losing?

00:09:34.990 --> 00:09:38.990
Umamusume

00:09:34.990 --> 00:09:38.990
{\an2}Pretty Derby

00:09:41.220 --> 00:09:43.950
Mejiro Palmer and Daitaku Helios are 
seriously outrunning the competition.

00:09:43.950 --> 00:09:46.800
There are ten lengths between them 
and the third-place runner!

00:09:46.800 --> 00:09:51.420
They'll need to close in soon to stand 
any chance against the two in the lead!

00:09:51.730 --> 00:09:54.430
Is Tokai Teio going to be 
all right in her position?

00:09:54.430 --> 00:09:58.040
She's had a lot of big ups and 
downs in her races recently.

00:09:58.040 --> 00:09:59.370
It's a bit worrying.

00:09:59.870 --> 00:10:02.850
Ow... I think I hit my rear 
on the way out of the gate.

00:10:04.010 --> 00:10:06.520
I can't win the Triple 
Crown or be undefeated.

00:10:06.520 --> 00:10:08.770
I can't be like the Prez anymore.

00:10:08.770 --> 00:10:11.900
So why am I even running anymore?

00:10:13.690 --> 00:10:15.060
Let's go, Helios!

00:10:15.060 --> 00:10:15.480
Yo!

00:10:15.480 --> 00:10:17.360
Come on!

00:10:20.910 --> 00:10:23.310
Why are they trying so hard?

00:10:24.430 --> 00:10:27.580
Tokai Teio is remaining steady, 
five to six positions from the rear.

00:10:27.580 --> 00:10:30.570
I don't think Teio-san's 
feeling well yet.

00:10:30.570 --> 00:10:31.830
No, this is fine.

00:10:31.830 --> 00:10:34.470
How, exactly?! Can't you 
see how far back she is?!

00:10:34.470 --> 00:10:37.680
There are things you can only 
learn by running in a race.

00:10:38.560 --> 00:10:41.300
You need to use this chance 
to figure it out, Teio!

00:10:42.500 --> 00:10:45.270
If I move further up, will I understand?

00:10:46.150 --> 00:10:48.540
Why the others are running?

00:10:49.260 --> 00:10:52.460
And why I should run?

00:10:52.460 --> 00:10:55.700
Coming around the fourth corner, 
and Mejiro Palmer is going for it.

00:10:55.700 --> 00:10:58.820
There's a 310 meter straightaway left, 
with the Nakayama course being a short one.

00:10:58.820 --> 00:11:00.280
You've got this!

00:11:00.280 --> 00:11:03.070
We're BFFs!

00:11:00.570 --> 00:11:03.070
Lyric Earth is moving 
up and narrowing the lead!

00:11:03.070 --> 00:11:04.640
And Nice Nature is closing 
in from the outside!

00:11:04.640 --> 00:11:07.700
And Mejiro Palmer and 
Lyric Earth cross the goal!

00:11:09.910 --> 00:11:13.580
Oh yeah! I did it! Helios!

00:11:21.970 --> 00:11:23.840
Nice job, Ikuno!

00:11:22.380 --> 00:11:25.260
Congratulations on third place, Nature-san!

00:11:37.570 --> 00:11:39.010
I couldn't make it.

00:11:39.810 --> 00:11:42.370
Teio-san... in 11th place?

00:11:42.370 --> 00:11:43.650
Oh, damn.

00:11:43.650 --> 00:11:46.140
I thought it was supposed to work out.

00:11:46.140 --> 00:11:47.470
I've got somewhere to be.

00:11:47.470 --> 00:11:48.820
Where are you going?

00:11:48.820 --> 00:11:50.510
Let him go, Spe.

00:11:50.510 --> 00:11:51.290
But...

00:11:55.120 --> 00:11:56.380
Ow, ow, ow...

00:11:57.650 --> 00:11:58.870
Damn it.

00:12:04.780 --> 00:12:09.060
I thought I had lost everything, but...

00:12:09.630 --> 00:12:14.460
I'm glad... I can still be 
frustrated after losing.

00:12:16.650 --> 00:12:20.600
Damn it! Damn it!

00:12:20.600 --> 00:12:21.570
Good.

00:12:22.490 --> 00:12:24.950
TOKAI TEIO INJURED

00:12:24.950 --> 00:12:26.910
TOKAI TEIO INJURED

00:12:28.660 --> 00:12:30.620
Tokai Teio Injured Again!

00:12:30.620 --> 00:12:32.620
Tokai Teio <font color="#fbfc63">Injured!
<font size="16" color="#b95a74">Injury to Left Gluteus Medius Will Require Protracted Rehab</font></font>

00:12:32.880 --> 00:12:34.410
What exactly is this?

00:12:34.410 --> 00:12:37.380
You get to be Spica's team leader!

00:12:34.410 --> 00:12:38.630
I am the leader

00:12:37.380 --> 00:12:38.630
Leader?

00:12:38.630 --> 00:12:40.600
That's right. From now on, you're going to be

00:12:40.600 --> 00:12:44.090
supporting the rest of 
the team as its leader.

00:12:45.140 --> 00:12:47.470
So I'm not a racer anymore?

00:12:48.180 --> 00:12:51.060
Are you trying to say 
I don't need to run anymore?

00:12:51.060 --> 00:12:52.060
No, no!

00:12:52.060 --> 00:12:55.530
There are some things you can only figure out 
by working to help others, that's all.

00:12:55.530 --> 00:12:57.490
I don't even know what you're talking about.

00:12:57.490 --> 00:12:58.960
Now, hang on!

00:12:58.960 --> 00:13:02.790
This is something that you'll need 
to start winning races again!

00:13:02.790 --> 00:13:04.760
Win... races?

00:13:05.400 --> 00:13:09.590
It's the kind of thing that you can't 
really understand without doing it.

00:13:09.590 --> 00:13:11.870
Come on! Think of it as an 
experiment or something.

00:13:14.700 --> 00:13:16.620
So what am I supposed to do?

00:13:17.420 --> 00:13:20.130
Sweets! Sweets! Sweets!

00:13:25.380 --> 00:13:27.930
Why am I doing this?

00:13:27.930 --> 00:13:30.590
Whoa, this one's a total mess!

00:13:31.050 --> 00:13:34.060
{\an8}Spe's

00:13:38.520 --> 00:13:41.310
Am I seriously supposed to make this many?

00:13:42.120 --> 00:13:44.570
Then again, I guess I ate a bunch, too.

00:13:45.190 --> 00:13:46.900
Vodka's

00:13:46.900 --> 00:13:49.870
Why's Vodka got so many towels?!

00:13:51.060 --> 00:13:52.330
Leader!

00:13:52.330 --> 00:13:55.290
{\an7}D.S.'S

00:13:52.770 --> 00:13:55.290
Ugh, that's even more than Vodka's!

00:13:55.290 --> 00:13:57.980
Hey, is being a leader really about 
doing a bunch of crummy chores?!

00:13:57.980 --> 00:13:59.540
Hey, they're not crummy at all.

00:13:59.540 --> 00:14:02.130
Horseshoes, diet, laundry...

00:14:02.130 --> 00:14:04.960
It's all stuff necessary to run well.

00:14:06.420 --> 00:14:09.720
Once you're done, go check 
the others out as they run,

00:14:09.720 --> 00:14:10.990
Leader.

00:14:12.270 --> 00:14:14.420
I'm not sure I buy any of this.

00:14:19.370 --> 00:14:21.120
Trainer, I finished...

00:14:21.120 --> 00:14:22.150
Kick it up a notch!

00:14:32.270 --> 00:14:34.030
Good! Nice times.

00:14:36.020 --> 00:14:37.800
I won that time.

00:14:37.800 --> 00:14:39.290
No, me!

00:14:39.290 --> 00:14:41.090
Go get hydrated!

00:14:41.090 --> 00:14:43.090
Leader, could you hand them their drinks?

00:14:43.090 --> 00:14:44.470
Oh, okay.

00:14:44.470 --> 00:14:46.420
Spe, Golshi, you're next!

00:14:46.420 --> 00:14:47.270
Okay!

00:14:47.270 --> 00:14:48.340
You got it.

00:14:51.710 --> 00:14:53.160
I feel alive again!

00:14:53.160 --> 00:14:54.880
I know that I won just now.

00:14:54.880 --> 00:14:57.560
Give it a rest! I was faster!

00:14:58.850 --> 00:15:01.090
What do you think, Leader?!

00:15:01.090 --> 00:15:02.480
Hey...

00:15:02.890 --> 00:15:06.190
What are you two racing for?

00:15:06.190 --> 00:15:07.710
To beat her!

00:15:07.710 --> 00:15:09.150
Stop copying me!

00:15:09.150 --> 00:15:10.090
I'm not!

00:15:10.090 --> 00:15:11.410
But think about it.

00:15:11.410 --> 00:15:14.310
It's not like you're always gonna 
be in the same races, right?

00:15:14.310 --> 00:15:15.980
What about the rest of the time?

00:15:15.980 --> 00:15:18.750
Oh, that doesn't matter at all.

00:15:19.010 --> 00:15:21.580
I'd definitely win if it was the same race.

00:15:21.580 --> 00:15:24.330
But the other races still matter.

00:15:24.690 --> 00:15:29.000
That's right! You better bust your butt 
all the time if you want to beat me.

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:30.660
I could say the same thing!

00:15:30.660 --> 00:15:32.570
Beating you is easy mode!

00:15:32.570 --> 00:15:35.090
Well beating you, Vodka, is super easy mode!

00:15:34.010 --> 00:15:37.350
Come on, quit fighting!

00:15:37.660 --> 00:15:40.280
Do you suppose Leader-san 
is going to be okay?

00:15:40.280 --> 00:15:42.560
She's trying to find something.

00:15:41.470 --> 00:15:44.660
Beating you is super-duper-uber easy mode!

00:15:42.560 --> 00:15:44.660
Her reason for racing.

00:15:44.660 --> 00:15:47.820
Well beating you is super-mega-
ultra-hyper-max easy mode!

00:15:45.540 --> 00:15:47.160
Her reason for racing?

00:15:52.460 --> 00:15:54.700
Looks like everything's ready.

00:16:06.820 --> 00:16:09.080
Where the heck am I?

00:16:09.570 --> 00:16:11.420
Here

00:16:09.570 --> 00:16:11.420
{\an8}Road

00:16:09.570 --> 00:16:11.420
{\an1}Tracen
 Academy

00:16:10.970 --> 00:16:12.080
And what's this?

00:16:12.080 --> 00:16:13.550
A mission for our leader.

00:16:14.270 --> 00:16:15.890
I seriously don't get any of this.

00:16:15.890 --> 00:16:17.110
You will if you go.

00:16:17.110 --> 00:16:19.860
And remember, you're headed 
there as team leader.

00:16:19.860 --> 00:16:22.460
So make sure to keep that sash on.

00:16:25.230 --> 00:16:27.300
This has to be a prank.

00:16:27.300 --> 00:16:28.480
Excuse me—

00:16:28.480 --> 00:16:31.280
I'm not wearing it because 
I want to, I swear!

00:16:31.280 --> 00:16:32.950
You're Tokai Teio-san, right?

00:16:40.280 --> 00:16:41.560
Y-Yes.

00:16:41.560 --> 00:16:42.950
I knew it!

00:16:42.950 --> 00:16:45.100
I'm always rooting for you!

00:16:45.100 --> 00:16:47.100
Um, can I shake your hand?

00:16:47.950 --> 00:16:49.260
O-Okay...

00:16:49.820 --> 00:16:51.450
Thank you so much!

00:16:51.450 --> 00:16:53.260
I have something to brag 
to my friends about now.

00:16:54.430 --> 00:16:57.470
I'm curious, what are you the leader of?

00:16:57.470 --> 00:17:00.010
I-It's nothing, really!

00:17:02.020 --> 00:17:04.480
PARK VIEWING PLATFORM

00:17:02.590 --> 00:17:03.820
See you!

00:17:09.340 --> 00:17:12.190
Seriously, where am I?

00:17:16.850 --> 00:17:18.660
I've been awaiting your arrival.

00:17:20.240 --> 00:17:21.620
Butler-san?!

00:17:22.250 --> 00:17:26.210
Leader-sama, thank you 
for coming all this way.

00:17:26.210 --> 00:17:29.060
You scared me! I didn't 
recognize you at first.

00:17:29.060 --> 00:17:31.540
And you're calling me "Leader" too, huh?

00:17:31.540 --> 00:17:34.030
Right this way, Leader-sama.

00:17:40.310 --> 00:17:43.360
Uh, where are we going?

00:17:44.540 --> 00:17:46.040
Um...

00:17:46.040 --> 00:17:47.360
It's over there.

00:17:51.230 --> 00:17:53.350
What is this place?

00:17:54.360 --> 00:17:57.490
The Mejiro family's sanatorium.

00:17:59.140 --> 00:18:00.470
Um...

00:18:01.630 --> 00:18:03.010
Well...

00:18:03.660 --> 00:18:06.160
I'm not sure why I'm here.

00:18:10.610 --> 00:18:12.530
The young miss is expecting you.

00:18:19.380 --> 00:18:20.810
McQueen?

00:18:22.150 --> 00:18:25.120
Miss, I've brought Leader-sama to see you.

00:18:25.120 --> 00:18:27.240
Excellent work, Butler.

00:18:27.240 --> 00:18:29.800
Teio, one moment, please.

00:18:29.800 --> 00:18:31.310
R-Right.

00:18:31.980 --> 00:18:33.860
Ten more to go.

00:18:44.030 --> 00:18:45.990
<font color="#392c15">I am the leader</font>

00:18:46.910 --> 00:18:49.120
How are your injuries?

00:18:49.120 --> 00:18:53.560
Quite well. I'll be rejoining Spica shortly.

00:18:53.560 --> 00:18:56.800
I think I've gained muscle that 
will help with my running.

00:18:57.270 --> 00:18:58.970
I-I see.

00:19:10.000 --> 00:19:11.060
McQueen...

00:19:11.290 --> 00:19:12.670
What is it?

00:19:12.670 --> 00:19:17.130
McQueen, how can you... 
Why do you try so hard?

00:19:17.570 --> 00:19:21.170
Because I am only looking at my goal.

00:19:21.170 --> 00:19:22.060
Your goal?

00:19:22.530 --> 00:19:26.150
Currently, it's to become stronger 
than I was before my injury.

00:19:26.150 --> 00:19:30.000
After that, it will be defeating 
a certain opponent.

00:19:30.000 --> 00:19:32.020
I can't afford to dawdle.

00:19:32.820 --> 00:19:35.380
I didn't know you had someone like that.

00:19:35.380 --> 00:19:36.940
Is it strange?

00:19:36.940 --> 00:19:40.090
Well, you blew everyone 
away at the Tennoushou.

00:19:40.090 --> 00:19:43.190
They're calling you the 
greatest stayer in history!

00:19:43.190 --> 00:19:45.880
Who could you still want to beat?

00:19:45.880 --> 00:19:50.490
It's having someone I want to defeat 
that allows me to become stronger.

00:19:50.490 --> 00:19:51.430
Stronger?

00:19:51.430 --> 00:19:52.860
Much stronger.

00:19:53.330 --> 00:19:55.520
I'm quite greedy, I'm afraid.

00:19:55.520 --> 00:19:58.260
So I intend to become much, much stronger,
 as far as I can take it.

00:20:00.700 --> 00:20:04.880
And so, I hope you'll 
make your comeback soon.

00:20:10.760 --> 00:20:13.260
Wait, is the person you want to beat...

00:20:14.040 --> 00:20:19.550
I had never been disappointed by how strong 
an opponent seemed before.

00:20:31.990 --> 00:20:35.770
It's true that I won the Spring Tennoushou.

00:20:36.130 --> 00:20:40.250
Thirty-two hundred meters on turf... 
A distance I specialize in.

00:20:41.460 --> 00:20:45.610
But we haven't competed over the 
distance you specialize in yet.

00:20:45.610 --> 00:20:47.870
My distance?

00:20:47.870 --> 00:20:50.780
I'm sure there's a distance 
that you're best suited to,

00:20:50.780 --> 00:20:53.290
much like how I'm called a stayer.

00:20:53.950 --> 00:20:56.120
A distance I'm good at...

00:20:56.120 --> 00:20:59.870
It wouldn't be fair unless we 
raced over that distance, too.

00:21:00.380 --> 00:21:02.690
As a horse girl of the Mejiro family,

00:21:02.690 --> 00:21:05.740
I cannot claim glory unless 
my victory is complete.

00:21:07.140 --> 00:21:10.380
Next time, I will crush you, 
at your best distance.

00:21:10.860 --> 00:21:14.800
So wipe that hollow look off your face.

00:21:15.310 --> 00:21:19.980
Your desire for victory, the same one 
every horse girl has, isn't gone, is it?

00:21:21.310 --> 00:21:27.540
From this moment on, I'd be glad to 
to run so as to be a goal for you.

00:21:38.330 --> 00:21:40.260
What's that look for?

00:21:40.260 --> 00:21:43.560
Well, since you're so set on it,
 I guess I could race you.

00:21:43.560 --> 00:21:45.970
But you might end up crying when you lose!

00:21:45.970 --> 00:21:49.730
I could easily say the same to you.

00:21:52.170 --> 00:21:54.640
I'm not gonna lose again!

00:21:55.320 --> 00:21:56.910
Challenge accepted.

00:21:59.850 --> 00:22:03.730
Incidentally, would you like 
to have your injury examined?

00:22:03.730 --> 00:22:06.910
Oh, have you forgotten how 
skilled my family's doctor is?

00:22:06.910 --> 00:22:08.850
I couldn't if I wanted to!

00:22:08.850 --> 00:22:11.280
U-Uh, let go!

00:22:11.280 --> 00:22:13.440
The preparations are already complete.

00:22:13.440 --> 00:22:14.990
D-Don't tell me...

00:22:14.990 --> 00:22:16.310
I'm the doctor.

00:22:16.310 --> 00:22:17.710
There he is!

00:22:17.950 --> 00:22:21.180
Please, enjoy a special course 
of the Mejiro family's treatment.

00:22:21.830 --> 00:22:23.700
Now, let's move along.

00:22:23.700 --> 00:22:25.710
W-Wait a second!

00:22:29.470 --> 00:22:32.170
Hang on! Why's he got a needle?!

00:22:32.170 --> 00:22:34.380
Because I'm the young lady's doctor.

00:22:34.380 --> 00:22:36.970
What is even happening?!

